Sixteen persons, including nine children, sustained injuries in a multiple auto crash in Umunya in Oyi Local Government Area of Anambra State. The incident which occurred on Wednesday evening, involved a Mack truck and Toyota Hiace bus with 20 passengers on board. The Nation gathered that the crash was as a result of wrongful overtaking which led to head-on collision of the two vehicles. Confirming the incident, Sector Commander, Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), Andrew Kumapayi said no death was recorded. He warned motorists to avoid wrongful overtaking by ensuring they only overtake when and where it is safe to do so .